research_municipality_step.notes: Bloomfield Township, NJ operates under a Special Charter with a Mayor and a six-member Township Council. The Mayor and three Council members are elected at-large, and three members are elected from each of three wards. Jenny Mundell was sworn in as Mayor in November 2024. Rosalee Gonzalez and Widney Polynice were sworn in to fill vacancies in December 2024.
